          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript used for public or private recitation, prayer, and contemplation. The title translated into English is Garland of jewels in the form of questions and answers. The work is written in poetic verse and asks religious and philosophical questions about the nature of the world and one's place in it; raises issues such as the cycle of life and death and one's ultimate release from it, especially if one recites the poem. Sometimes the text is attributed to Śaṅkarācārya.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Praśnottararatnamālā</title>
              <title type="vernacular">प्रश्नोत्तररत्नमाला</title>
